item.title: Compiler Help Please?
item.dc:creator: @swebbyscape swebbyscape
item.description:
@swebbyscape wrote:

Go to Start Click MY Computer, or Computer, go into your hard drive and scroll down to program files. If it has a “(x86)” next to it you need to put that into the compiler. So it knows where to find you JDK. If this is the Case is should look something like this:

@echo off Title Compiler "C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jdk1.6.0_21\bin\javac.exe" *.java pause
